CCTV footage has been released of the vehicle allegedly involved in the kidnapping of a 6-year-old Grade R pupil from the front of Laerskool Kollegepark in Vanderbijlpark on Monday morning. The kidnappers of Amy-Lee de Jager are demanding R2m for her release. Four men kidnapped the child in front of the Gauteng school at around 07:40 on Monday, loaded her into a white Toyota Fortuner and drove off with her. Police spokesperson Captain Kay Makhubele told News24 a manhunt has been launched. Pictures of a white Toyota Fortuner with a GP registration plate, which have been circulating, is not the vehicle that was used in the kidnapping. The vehicle, which has no number plates, was last seen on the R82 close to Meyerton, Netwerk24 reported. UPDATE | R2m ransom demanded for kidnapped Grade R girl - Compiled by Kate Henry     GET THE NEWS at your fingertips and download the News24 app for Android or iPhone. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter